    • Method Detail

      • get

        IObjectParameter get(String type)
        Gets the object parameter with the given type contained in this container. If no such parameter is contained in this container, null is returned.
        Parameters:
        type - the type of the parameter to get
        Returns:
        the object parameter with the given name, or null, if no such parameter is contained in this container

      • get

        <T extends IObjectParameter> T get(String type,
                                   Class<T> clazz)
        Gets the object parameter with the given type contained in this container and casts the result to the given object parameter type. If no such parameter is contained in this container, null is returned.
        Type Parameters:
        T - type of the parameter
        Parameters:
        type - the type of the parameter to get
        clazz - the class of the parameter to get
        Returns:
        the object parameter with the given type and object parameter type, or null, if no such parameter is contained in this container
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if the cast to object parameter type fails

      • add

        void add(IObjectParameter objectParameter)
        Adds the specified object parameter to this container.

        Preconditions: The object parameter

        • must be a root parameter (i.e. the result of IObjectParameter.getRootSchemaId() must not be null)
        • root schema id must no already exists in this container.
        • must not already be attached to another container.
        Parameters:
        objectParameter - the object parameter to add
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if preconditions are not met

      • remove

        IObjectParameter remove(String type)
        Removes the object parameter of the specified type from this container.
        Parameters:
        type - the type of object parameter to remove
        Returns:
        the removed object parameter , or null if the given type doesn't exist.

      • size

        int size()
        Returns:
        the number of elements in this container

      • areValid

        boolean areValid()
        Returns:
        true if all object parameters in this container are valid, or false, otherwise
